article.description: N. Dakota St. 78, S. Dakota St. 60
article.headline: N. Dakota St. 78, S. Dakota St. 60
article.linkText: N. Dakota St. 78, S. Dakota St. 60
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. (AP) -- Mike Nelson scored 24 points and Brett Winkelman added 21 as North Dakota State won its sixth straight game, beating South Dakota State 78-60 on Saturday. The Bison (14-6) had lost five straight games at SDSU. But they brought that streak to an end by shooting a blistering 60 percent from the field against the Jackrabbits. Nelson was 9-for-10 from the floor and made all four of his 3-point attempts. NDSU was 7-for-10 from 3-point range. SDSU (5-17) shot just 35 percent from the field and made only five of 15 3-pointers. Four NDSU players reached double figures. Ben Woodside had 16 points and Andre Smith added 12. Nelson made a 3-pointer midway through the second half to cap a 13-0 run that gave the Bison control of the game. SDSU led 9-8 with 15:41 to play in the first half, but the Bison strung together their first big run, a 16-4 spurt to go up 22-13. They stretched the lead to 14 points with 3:49 left in the half. NDSU made 11 of its first 13 shots from the field and shot 64 percent in the first half. SDSU, which shot just 37 percent from field in the first half, rallied late. Mackenzie Casey's 3-pointer as time ran out in the half cut the deficit to 38-33. The Jackrabbits scored the last eight points of the half. SDSU got within three points right away in the second half, but the Bison quickly stretched the lead to double figures and kept it there with clutch shooting. Winkelman made nine of 14 shots and Woodside was 6-for-11 in the game. Kai Williams scored 17 points and grabbed nine rebounds for the Jackrabbits. Casey added 10 points and Michael Loney had a game-high 11 rebounds. The game was the first of five straight road games for the Bison.
